{
    "m_SGVersion": 0,
    "m_Type": "UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData",
    "m_ObjectId": "cb56fbae305241889d87f596d1aae55d",
    "m_Title": "4. Noise + UV -> Height map",
    "m_Content": "We want to achieve a Height map defining the dunes in our material. \nTo make our material more versatile, we add Tiling support: create a Tiling and Offset node, and a new Vector 2 parameter UV Tiling which we will feed into the Tiling pin of the new node. Now, take the tiled UV coordinates and sum with the outputs of Step 1 and 3.\nTake the result of this operation and feed it through a Fraction node, which will return the decimal part. \nFinally, create a Custom Function node: we will use a code function in the Shader Graph, because we need a feature which isn't supported natively by ShaderGraph. Select your Custom Function node and find the Graph Inspector on the right. Here, ensure that the Type option is set to File: then, write \"PolygonGradient\" for Name and find the Shading file in the Source asset box. Lastly, create 4 inputs and 1 output: in order, these need to have the following names and types:\n\r\nUV - Vector 2\r\nSides - Float\r\nWidth - Float\r\nHeight - Float\r\n\r\nOut - Float",
    "m_TextSize": 0,
    "m_Theme": 0,
    "m_Position": {
        "serializedVersion": "2",
        "x": -2449.0,
        "y": 1145.0,
        "width": 822.0,
        "height": 239.0
    },
    "m_Group": {
        "m_Id": ""
    }
}

